800–1800 m asl) consisted of mixed forests dominated by Abies alba (inferred from the abundance of its macrofossils at Lago Verdarolo; Figure 2) with a diverse array of broadleaved deciduous trees (Figure 3) but probably low abundances of the most thermophilous species (for example, submediterranean Quercus), and (2) the lower belt (
