2500 mm). Indeed, the results of RDA and GAM suggest the dominant tree species (for example, Abies alba, Ulmus, Fraxinus excelsior, Tilia, Acer) to have been rather sensitive to fire (Figures 3B, 4, S4), in agreement with previous short-term post-fire monitoring (for example, Delarze and others 1992; Hofmann and others 1998; Thomas 2016; Thomas and others 2018) and long-term paleoecological studies (for example, Tinner and others 1999, 2000; Rey and others 2019).
